        g: '09315000', avg: 5200, histFlow: 4800, mx: 225, my: 250, abbr: 'UT',
        desc: "Eighty-four miles of wilderness whitewater through the deepest canyon in the Uinta Basin — deeper than the Grand Canyon at its maximum point. Desolation Canyon is one of the great multi-day river trips in North America: Class I–III rapids through 2,000 feet of layered sandstone, cottonwood groves sheltering ancient Fremont rock art, bighorn sheep on every cliff band, and not a road or power line for the entire run.",
