        g: '07211500', avg: 250, histFlow: 220, mx: 275, my: 355, abbr: 'NM',
        desc: "The Canadian River flows through the plains and mesas of northeastern New Mexico, carving through volcanic basalt canyons on its way to the Texas border. Eighty miles of gentle Class I–II water through a remote high-plains landscape with pronghorn, mule deer, and raptors.",
