        g: '10293000', avg: 75, histFlow: 68, mx: 130, my: 220, abbr: 'NV',
        desc: "A premier Western fly-fishing destination known for trophy brown trout. The East Walker below Bridgeport Reservoir is a tailwater that produces some of the largest brown trout in the Great Basin. Cold, clear water through sagebrush desert makes this a wade-fishing paradise.",
        desig: 'Nevada Trophy Trout Water · Bridgeport Reservoir Tailwater',
