        co: 'Elko Co.', len: '30 mi', cls: 'I–II', opt: '20–100',
        g: '13162500', avg: 45, histFlow: 40, mx: 130, my: 220, abbr: 'NV',
        desc: "One of the most remote rivers in the lower 48 states, flowing through the Jarbidge Wilderness in northeastern Nevada. The Jarbidge supports native bull trout and Lahontan cutthroat in a pristine mountain canyon accessible only by long dirt roads. A true wilderness experience.",
