        desc: "Northeast Ohio's best whitewater river — the Grand carves through a dramatic shale gorge in the upper reaches before widening into a scenic corridor flowing north to Lake Erie. Ohio Scenic River designated, with Class II–III ledge drops in the gorge section near Harpersfield.",
