        desc: "The upper Farmington is Connecticut's only National Wild and Scenic River — 14 miles of dam-release whitewater and world-class fly fishing through the Farmington Valley. The Tariffville Gorge section delivers Class III rapids minutes from Hartford, making it the most accessible serious paddling in the state.",
