        desc: "Central Connecticut's urban-to-wild river flows 38 miles from the Hanging Hills of Meriden past Sleeping Giant State Park to New Haven Harbor. The Quinnipiac has undergone a remarkable environmental recovery — once severely polluted, it now supports paddling, fishing, and wildlife viewing through an increasingly green corridor. Sleeping Giant's traprock ridge towers above the river.",
