        desc: "The gem of Connecticut's Quiet Corner — the Natchaug flows through Natchaug State Forest in eastern Connecticut with Class I–II rapids, swimming holes, and the legendary Diana Pool. The river's hemlock-shaded gorges and clean water make it feel more like northern New England than southern Connecticut.",
