        desc: "The Pawcatuck River forms the Rhode Island / Connecticut border, flowing from freshwater swamps to tidal estuary at Westerly. Gentle Class I–II paddling through diverse habitats — cedar swamp, deciduous forest, salt marsh. One of the most ecologically varied short river trips in New England.",
