        desc: "The Patapsco flows 39 miles from the Piedmont through the heart of Patapsco Valley State Park before reaching Baltimore Harbor. The state park protects over 30 miles of river corridor with historic mill towns, stone arch railroad bridges, and Class I–II paddling through hemlock-lined gorges. The 2018 Bloede Dam removal — the largest dam removal in Maryland history — restored migratory fish runs to the lower river for the first time in over a century.",
