        desc: "New England's premier dam-release whitewater river. The Deerfield delivers Class II–IV rapids through the Berkshire Hills on scheduled releases from Fife Brook Dam — the most reliable whitewater in Massachusetts. The Dryway section pushes Class IV during high releases. Below Charlemont, the river mellows through covered-bridge farm country.",
