        desc: "Massachusetts's first National Wild and Scenic River. The Westfield flows through the Berkshire foothills with Class I–III whitewater on multiple branches. The North Branch through Chesterfield Gorge is the signature section — a granite gorge with technical rapids in a state-managed forest.",
        desig: "National Wild & Scenic River (1993, first in MA) · Chesterfield Gorge",
